//lecture 6 :dom
//DOM allows JavaScript to control, read, and change the web page after it‚Äôs loaded ‚Äî without reloading it.
//So basically, DOM makes web pages dynamic and interactive, instead of just plain static HTML.
// it is used to access the html element and change it's content dynamically
//DOM connects HTML (structure) and JavaScript (logic) so that your web page can react, change, and feel alive üí´
